Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.93,0:00:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Dr. David Hawkins. I've been a psychiatrist for the last 35 years,\Na psychoanalyst, nutritionist, researcher into brain chemistry and its relationship to nutrition.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.44,0:00:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And for the last seven years I've been doing research into the nature of consciousness itself\Nand its application to spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.32,0:00:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this series we are looking at the application of the knowledge\Nderived from this study of the nature of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.32,0:00:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to human problems.\NIn this particular talk today we'll be talking about sexuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.41,0:00:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be talking about the difference between sex and making love,\Nbetween high and low energy sex,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.95,0:01:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,how to transcend being guilty and at the effect of social programming about sexuality,\Nhow to experience it from the heart instead of just from the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.19,0:01:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,how to make it an uplifting and grand experience\Nrather than one of manipulation and control,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.01,0:01:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,how to get out of the energy interactions which result in impotence and frigidity\Nand sexual dysfunction.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.40,0:01:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll ask the question, does God approve of sex?\NIs sex all over with advancing age?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.86,0:01:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Does middle age mean you're over the hill?\NThese and other questions as we address it from the viewpoint of consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.95,0:01:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be talking from that position,\Nfrom the viewpoint of body, mind and spirit,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.73,0:01:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,about which we have heard so much in the field of holistic health.\NIs that a slogan? Is that a catchphrase?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.73,0:01:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it mean, body, mind and spirit?\NWhat is spirit anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.80,0:01:59.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it something we can experience?\NIs there an energy to that that we can discover through our own inner research
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.80,0:02:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and to our own inner experiences?\NSo we'll be talking today about our own inner experiences,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.80,0:02:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,subtle states,\Ninner awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.80,0:02:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and the part they play in this important area of human behavior.\NBefore we do that, we want to get into the nature
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.85,0:02:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of the relationship between body and mind and spirit.\NWe want to review where it is that human experience is experienced,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.04,0:02:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,talk a little bit about consciousness itself,\Ndemystify it,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.04,0:02:38.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and turn it into something understandable.\NTo help us to do that, we'll be referring to a chart
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.14,0:02:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,on the blackboard here,\Nwhich we've used in others of this series,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.36,0:02:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,referring to the levels of consciousness.\NWe have a mathematical model that has come out of our research,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.36,0:03:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,which is very helpful in understanding\Nthe nature of the relationship between body, mind and spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.20,0:03:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll review briefly what is that relationship.\NAnd we begin by looking at the fact that the body itself
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.87,0:03:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,cannot experience itself.\NWhen we're talking about sexuality, everybody automatically thinks
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.87,0:03:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the body and its allure and all the physicality of form.\NAnd astonishingly enough, when we look at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.64,0:03:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we realize that the body itself is in ascension.\NThat is, it cannot experience itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.64,0:03:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The arm cannot experience its armness.\NThe leg cannot experience its legness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.12,0:03:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Something else, something greater than that,\Nhas to take place before experience happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.12,0:03:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So the body is experienced through sensations.\NSensations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.12,0:03:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What we experience is not the body,\Nbut the sensations of the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.12,0:03:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,where it is in space and where it is in motion.\NThe sensations themselves cannot really experience themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.66,0:04:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to be experienced in something larger,\Nand that is in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.66,0:04:07.79,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at it carefully,\Nwe realize we are not experiencing the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.79,0:04:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not really experiencing the sensations of the body.\NWe're experiencing what is going on in mind about the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.98,0:04:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind itself, curiously enough, cannot experience itself.\NA thought doesn't experience its thoughtness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.49,0:04:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A feeling doesn't experience its feelingness.\NSomething larger than mind has to be present,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.65,0:04:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,something that is unchanging in itself.\NAnd so what is going on in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.65,0:04:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,the reason we become aware of that,\Nis because of consciousness itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.65,0:04:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a much larger energy field.\NThan that of mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.07,0:04:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We're aware of what is going on in mind,\Nthen, because of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.07,0:04:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind is telling us what is going on in emotions,\Nthoughts, sensations.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.07,0:04:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensations are telling us what is going on in body.\NTherefore, what we're experiencing,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.00,0:05:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then, is always going on in the field of consciousness itself,\Nwhich is like an invisible screen
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.00,0:05:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that is really located everywhere.\NConsciousness itself is really unaware
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.00,0:05:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is happening within itself.\NIt is because of something infinitely larger
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.00,0:05:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,than even consciousness itself,\Nand that is awareness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.00,0:05:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of awareness itself,\Nthat which has no dimension,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.00,0:05:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,no locality.\NAnd so we're experiencing experience, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.00,0:05:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,within the field of consciousness itself,\Nin handling human problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.09,0:05:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,behavioral problems,\Nunderstanding human behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.09,0:05:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,We can address it, then, directly\Nby going
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.09,0:05:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to its experience within consciousness itself.\NBecause consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.73,0:05:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is more powerful and more dominant,\Nwe can handle problems that seem to be
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.73,0:05:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,arising in the body by handling them\Non the level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.73,0:06:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,on the level of mind.\NAnd that's what we'll be doing today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.73,0:06:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be looking at human experience and events.\NAnd we'll be seeing that events are one thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.40,0:06:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but how we choose to be with them\Nis something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.40,0:06:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We may not be able to determine or control\Nor choose the events that occur in our life,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.40,0:06:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,but we can determine how we wish to be with them.\NAnd therefore, the experience of how to be with that
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.40,0:06:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is perhaps more important than the event.\NWe all know that in a certain mood,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.53,0:06:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,a trivial, you know, an irritation may be trivial.\NWe know that in another mood,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.53,0:06:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that same event can be aggravating\Nor even send us into a rage.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.53,0:06:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, how we are with that,\Nand that brings up the whole concept of energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.92,0:06:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy field, the position from which\Nwe're coming about a situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.11,0:06:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the way we are holding our own existence,\Nthe importance of all events
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.11,0:07:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of the context\Ncreated by our position.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.11,0:07:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we'll be referring to this chart,\Nwhich we referred to in other talks,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.11,0:07:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,in which we have these levels of consciousness,\Nand each of these levels
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.30,0:07:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,has been calibrated\Nas to their relative energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.30,0:07:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the power of that energy field,\Ncalibrated mathematically,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.30,0:07:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,which gives us an understanding\Nin our left brain way of understanding things.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.30,0:07:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Each of them has a direction of an energy field,\Nwhether it is negative or positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.30,0:07:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of these energy fields come emotions,\Nwhich we'll be referring to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.30,0:07:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of these energy fields\Ncomes a way of viewing the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.30,0:07:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a view of...\Na way of relating to that
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.30,0:07:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,which is greater than our individual self,\Nand a process that is going on in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.88,0:07:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll pull this all together then,\Nwe'll pull this all together
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.88,0:07:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,as we address the questions\Nof high energy sex,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.88,0:08:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is coming out of the heart,\Nthat which is coming out of our way of being in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.88,0:08:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and low energy sex,\Nwhich is localized in a physical kind of an experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.88,0:08:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,about which society has had so much to say over the ages.\NHow to resolve the conflicts
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.88,0:08:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that come out of holding it from that position.\NAnd we'll see that man's conflict about sexuality
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.88,0:08:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of the energy field\Nof his position about that,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.04,0:08:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,how he perceives it,\Nwhat it means to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.04,0:08:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Problems are best solved\Nnot on the level at which they appear to be occurring,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.04,0:08:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but on the next level above them.\NSo today we're not going to be talking about philosophy,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.16,0:08:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to be talking about clinical experience,\Nthat which you can verify through your own experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.16,0:08:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,through human experience.\NWe're going to look at the area of problems
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.16,0:08:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,from a level that is above the problems.\NSo problems are best solved
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.16,0:09:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,by transcending them\Nand looking at them from a higher viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.16,0:09:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,in which very often\Nbecause there's a shift of point of view
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.16,0:09:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the problem automatically resolves\Nor we see that there wasn't any to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.16,0:09:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we want to go back to\Nwhat is the difference between high and low energy sex
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.55,0:09:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and see how what man considers sexual problems\Nare coming really out of an energy field itself
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.55,0:09:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and how we can change our position with that.\NWhat can we do about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.55,0:09:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In general, when people talk about sex\Nthey are referring to a type of experience
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.38,0:09:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but they are talking considerably\Nabout an energy field which everybody presumes
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.38,0:09:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and which Madison Avenue plays on called desire.\NWhat they are talking about is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.38,0:09:51.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain perception,\Na certain way of looking at things,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.38,0:09:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,a certain wantingness,\Nthe overcoming of a frustration,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.38,0:10:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the overcoming of lack,\Nthe withholding of this,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.38,0:10:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the manipulation of this,\Nthe gratifying of it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.38,0:10:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the using it as trade in relationships,\Nthe allure, the price,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.38,0:10:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the value added to this allure,\Nand to the physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.38,0:10:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So in general, man is talking about physicality.\NAnd from there, because of the physicality,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.38,0:10:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,then he gets into the field of morality.\NAnd so morality is coming out of physicality,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.38,0:10:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,holding sexuality from the physical level,\Nfrom the lower energy fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.38,0:10:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have the story of the Garden of Eden\Nand what happens in the Garden of Eden.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.38,0:10:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens in the Garden of Eden\Nis the man and the woman,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.96,0:10:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in a state of innocence,\Nin a very high energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.96,0:10:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,eat of the tree of knowledge,\Neat of the tree of good and evil.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.96,0:10:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They buy into a world of duality.\NYou see, in the world of love,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.96,0:11:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no duality.\NIn lovingness, lovingness just is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.96,0:11:08.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The heart doesn't say anything.\NThe heart just knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.96,0:11:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The heart is with life.\NIn eating of the tree of right and wrong, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.11,0:11:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and good and evil,\Nthen what happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.11,0:11:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then what happened is they saw themselves as bodies.\NThey came down into guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.11,0:11:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, guilt is at the bottom.\NSo from a high state of joy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.11,0:11:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that state of lovingness,\Ninfinite being with life out of joy,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.11,0:11:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,which is beyond right and wrong,\Nit doesn't even arise,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.59,0:11:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,they fell into a field\Nin which they were looking at the body as a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.59,0:11:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As a body, they then became conscious of its bodiness\Nand out of that arose man's sexual problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.59,0:12:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So whether it's historically an event or not is immaterial.\NPsychologically, it is an event that has happened to mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.26,0:12:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the problems that man calls sexual\Nare really due to a
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.26,0:12:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,point of view,\Na point of view about physicality,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.26,0:12:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing sexuality as a physical phenomena,\Nbeing run by the desire of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.26,0:12:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the opposite side of the coin of desire?\NAversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.26,0:12:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And so sexuality is then characterized by desiring this.\NIt's characterized by aversion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.26,0:12:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's characterized by avoiding the field,\Nwanting nothing to do with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.26,0:12:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,taking a moralistic position about that,\Nthat one is now superior to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.26,0:12:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Superior to what?\NSuperior to seeing it as an animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.26,0:12:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,physical function.\NIt even degrades that which is the animal,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.26,0:12:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and calls it animal as though\Nthe animal world which is
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.26,0:13:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and was created by God\Nis somehow immoral,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.26,0:13:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,calling it animal.\NSo what is the difficulty then?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.39,0:13:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty is not in sexuality at all, is it?\NThe difficulty is within consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.39,0:13:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's how mind is holding what sexuality is.\NIt's arising out of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.39,0:13:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,how in consciousness the mind is seeing sexuality,\Nand how it defines these relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.39,0:13:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,We know from our study of these fields of consciousness\Nthat everything we call courage
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.25,0:13:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in an energy field of 200\Nwhere we see that this arrow is neutral,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.25,0:13:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's no longer negative,\Nwe see everything from this level down
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.25,0:13:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,as positions of victim,\Nas positions of coming from lack.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.25,0:13:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, guilt and apathy and grief and fear,\Ndesire, anger, pride,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.25,0:13:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,are all coming from positions of lack,\Nof not having wholeness,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.25,0:14:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,not being at one with life.\NAnd so, holding sexuality then from the physical level,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.41,0:14:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,dividing it according to gender\Ninto maleness and femaleness,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.41,0:14:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,creates a feeling of separation,\Nand out of that separation then comes desire,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.41,0:14:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that comes frustration,\Nout of the frustration comes anger and resentment,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.41,0:14:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of all that comes fear and grief and apathy.\NAnd so some people are into guilt over sexuality,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.41,0:14:31.41,Default,,0,0,0,,some people are into apathy,\Nhopelessness, lack of desire,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.41,0:14:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and some people are into grief,\Nsome people are into fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.41,0:14:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,people are into desiringness and wantingness\Nand being run by that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.41,0:14:44.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and anger over that,\Nor the endless pridefulness about sexuality,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.41,0:14:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the strutting one's macho image\Nor the sticking out of one's feminine attributes
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.41,0:14:55.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in a prideful and tantalizing,\Nseductive kind of controlling,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.41,0:15:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,manipulating, exploiting kind of way.\NAnd we see the marketing industry do this,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.41,0:15:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,use this desiringness,\Nuse this frustration, this lack,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.41,0:15:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,this feeling of separation,\Nto try to control people and manipulate them,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.41,0:15:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to have the pretty girl sitting on the hood of the car.\NYou see, what has a car got to do with a pretty girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.41,0:15:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It's trying to connect that.\NIf I get this car, if I get this shampoo,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.41,0:15:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,if I get this hairdo, if I wear this perfume,\Nthen I will overcome this separation
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.41,0:15:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,between myself and that which I desire.\NAnd so that point of view then
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.92,0:15:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is creating an endless painfulness,\Nan endless source of suffering,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.92,0:15:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and the suffering takes various forms.\NWhether it's impotence or frigidity
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.92,0:15:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or satiriasis, whatever the form may take.\NIt's coming out of holding sexuality from that view,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.92,0:15:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,from its physicalness, from its desiringness,\Nfrom its wantingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.50,0:16:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see how therefore one is run by that.\NWe see one nature of this energy field of desire,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.50,0:16:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the emotions accompanying that\Nare wantingness, cravingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.50,0:16:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to be addicted to.\NAnd we know people who become addicted
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.50,0:16:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to sex.\NSexuality is what runs them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.50,0:16:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's their whole thing.\NThe endless going to bed with everybody
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.50,0:16:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that is available.\NThe needing to prove one's desirability.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.85,0:16:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The needing to prove something.\NAnd so we see over on the right hand side
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.85,0:16:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the process going on in consciousness\Non this energy level.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.85,0:16:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called entrapment, entrapped.\NWithin consciousness, on this energy level,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.98,0:16:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,once you want something,\Nthat wanting begins to run you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.98,0:16:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The desiringness wants you.\NThe wantingness runs you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.98,0:16:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Temporary gratification.\NBecause of the negativity of this energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.98,0:16:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,which is endlessly frustrating,\Nendlessly wanting, endlessly craving,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.98,0:16:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the person still remains entrapped.\NThere is no completion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.98,0:17:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no feeling of finality.\NThere is no feeling of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.33,0:17:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that happiness does not occur\Nuntil you get up to an energy field of about 500.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.33,0:17:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore trying to find happiness\Nthrough the endless creation and satisfaction,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.33,0:17:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the cycling of this desire,\Nthe release of the frustration.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.33,0:17:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally frustration feels good\Nwhen you temporarily satisfy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.33,0:17:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels good when you stop banging your head\Nagainst the wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.33,0:17:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is not the same thing as happiness.\NThe desiringness, the cravingness continues on.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.33,0:17:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It is because of this then,\Nbecause of this physicality,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.33,0:17:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the energy field,\Nthat all the moral questions arise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.33,0:17:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does religion,\Nwhy does morality address itself
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.33,0:17:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to this kind of an energy field?\NWhy is it called carnal?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.33,0:17:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It is called carnal because\Nit is like lower energy sexuality
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.33,0:18:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of the lower energy fields of the body\Nbeing held in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.33,0:18:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in a lower viewpoint.\NAnd therefore the whole question of morality
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.33,0:18:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,then addresses itself really to that\Nwhich is carnality.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.33,0:18:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Carnality in this case,\Nlooking down on one's animal nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.33,0:18:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of prizing it,\Ninstead of being happy,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.33,0:18:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of being grateful,\Ninstead of saying it is beautiful,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.33,0:18:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,it is being downgraded.\NAnd that which is intrinsically beautiful
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.33,0:18:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,when it is not judged\Nis held in a degrading manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.00,0:18:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How to get off this cycle,\Nhow to experience sexuality
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.00,0:18:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,from a much different energy field.\NHow to get released from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.10,0:18:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And that will take us back into\Na discussion then of how
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.10,0:18:52.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to let go,\Nhow to let go being at the effect of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.10,0:18:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How to let go being run by\Nthe cycling of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.10,0:19:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How to be with sexuality\Nfrom a different energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.10,0:19:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it is experienced\Nas a totally different experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.10,0:19:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When we hold it and look at it\Nfrom a different level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.20,0:19:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,all the questions and problems\Nnow disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.20,0:19:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing as manipulation.\NThere is no such thing as withholding,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.20,0:19:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,frustration, being run by desire,\Ngoing into anger and resentment over that,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.20,0:19:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,going into a feeling of lack.\NIf the desire is not fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.20,0:19:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,then what comes up?\NWhat comes up is a fear that it won't be fulfilled,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.20,0:19:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a grief that it hasn't been,\Nan apathy, an anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.20,0:19:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,a frustration, a self-blame.\NWe see that at the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.20,0:19:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,guilt is accompanied by self-hatred.\NWe see that holding sexuality
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.20,0:19:47.20,Default,,0,0,0,,from this level leads to a view\Nof the world of sin and suffering,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.20,0:19:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of hopelessness, of sadness.\NAnd sexuality, the whole subject,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.20,0:19:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes frightening.\NWe want to guard our children from this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.20,0:20:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes competitive\Nwhen sex is used in a seductive manner,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.20,0:20:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in a manipulative power field.\NWe have competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.20,0:20:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We have its use as a symbol of status.\NOne's sexual attraction
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.20,0:20:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,then becomes a status symbol.\NAnd the adornment of the human body,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.20,0:20:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,et cetera, becomes a symbol of status,\Nanother way of controlling and manipulating
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.20,0:20:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and trying to influence one's sense of self-worth.\NThe worry and the anxiety,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.20,0:20:32.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the wantingness, the resentment, the hatreds.\NAnd so we see that sexuality based on
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.20,0:20:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,this energy field often leads to hatred.\NAnd we have the stabbings
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.20,0:20:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the violent murders based on\Nthat infatuation, that seduction,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.20,0:20:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the manipulation of one by another\Nand the triangulations of these situations
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.20,0:20:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the unconscious exploitations that are going on\Nbased on this desiringness, this attractiveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.20,0:21:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We see the denial about this.\NWe see the contempt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.74,0:21:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we get up to pridefulness\Nbecause of the morality about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.74,0:21:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we get into contempt, we get into denial,\Nwe get into religious conflict,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.74,0:21:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,we get into people who hold all sexuality\Nfrom a contemptuous,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.74,0:21:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,looking down their nose at it\Nas though anybody who indulges in that kind of activity
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.74,0:21:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,must be coming from a low animal nature.\NThey presume that everyone else is run by it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.74,0:21:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in the same way that they are.\NPeople who hold contempt for it
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.77,0:21:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,are projecting their own way of being with it\Nonto others and saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.77,0:21:46.41,Default,,0,0,0,,aren't they carnal, aren't they animal, etc.\NHow to let go of that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.41,0:21:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll contrast that with a high energy sex\Nwith a different energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.41,0:21:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,with a different way of being with it\Nthat then transcends all these problems
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.41,0:22:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of competition, frustration,\Nof fright and guilt and regret
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.41,0:22:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and worry and anxiety.\NJust imagine, how can you enjoy yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.41,0:22:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in a human endeavor that is taking place\Nin this whole energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.41,0:22:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in which secretly you feel really\Nthat God is probably going to punish you for it
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.41,0:22:19.41,Default,,0,0,0,,because the view of God coming out of\Nthese energy fields is punitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.41,0:22:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,You are certainly separated from Him\Nand if you get any enjoyment or happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.41,0:22:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,very likely at the end there's going to be retaliation.\NSome people can't stand the intensity
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.41,0:22:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,of this conflict between\Nthe driving biologic urge,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.41,0:22:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the psychological need and religion\Nand so they just split out of it all together
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.41,0:22:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and jump into atheism\Nwhich just handles the whole thing that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.41,0:22:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,One has to either let go of one's\Nview of God and religion
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.41,0:22:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,or let go of one's sexuality.\NAnd so for some people it is an impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.41,0:22:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,conflict to resolve\Nand many people end up as atheistic
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.41,0:22:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,because there's no way they can handle\Ntheir humanness
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.41,0:23:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and also their views of God.\NHow can we move out of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.05,0:23:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we move away from being run by that\Nso that we can begin to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.05,0:23:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,this behavior, these experiences\Nfrom a different energy field?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.24,0:23:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll contrast it with\Nan energy field of lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.30,0:23:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Love as an expression,\NI mean sexuality as an expression
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.30,0:23:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of lovingness,\Nas a sense of aliveness,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.30,0:23:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of being with the truth of that which you are.\NIn order to experience that concept,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.81,0:23:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that kind of an experience,\Nwe have to let go of this lower
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.81,0:23:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,energy field\Nin which sex is experienced really
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.81,0:23:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,as a local physical phenomena.\NAnd most people, if you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.81,0:23:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,sit down and ask them,\Nif I ask them in the office,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.81,0:23:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,what is sexual experience to them,\Nis primarily a local physical phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.81,0:23:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you get all kinds of preoccupation\Nwith anatomy,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.81,0:24:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,immense preoccupation with their fitness\Nas a sexual partner,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.81,0:24:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and women's.\NFocusing on the physical attributes of the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.81,0:24:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And along with the physicalness of it\Ngoes emotionality,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.81,0:24:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,emotionality, sentimentality,\Nand emotionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.81,0:24:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And emotionality plus physicality then\Nis the expression of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.81,0:24:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The mad passionate embrace\Nand the expression of the emotionality
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.81,0:24:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,of wantingness and desiringness.\NOh how I want you,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.81,0:24:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I crave you,\Noh how I must have you,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.81,0:24:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and the thrill of all that.\NAnd this is what the movies portray, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.44,0:24:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If we let go of that,\Nwhat kind of an experience is possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.44,0:24:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of an experience is possible?\NWe'll contrast with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.44,0:24:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of an experience would happen\Nif it was no longer local,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.44,0:25:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,if it was no longer a negative energy field of 125?\NWhat would happen if it happened out of the heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.44,0:25:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,out of a positive energy field of 500,\Nout of the space of being with the reality
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.44,0:25:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and the truth of that which you are?\NFirst we'll have to talk about how to let go
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.15,0:25:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of this energy field then.\NHow to not be run by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.15,0:25:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,How to experience sex\Nwhen it's extremely appropriate,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.15,0:25:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,when there is no conflict.\NHow can we let go of this cravingness?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.34,0:25:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,If this energy field is what is causing all the problem,\Nthen how can we transcend it,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.34,0:25:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we can experience it from a much higher level?\NWe'll use a technique which is worked with weight problems,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.17,0:25:46.17,Default,,0,0,0,,which is worked with pain,\Nwhich is worked with illnesses of a great variety of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.17,0:25:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The basic principle works the same\Nno matter what we apply it to.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.17,0:25:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is when the energy,\Nwhen the feeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.24,0:25:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,when the expression,\Nwhen the desire comes up,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.24,0:26:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what we do is we let go labeling it\Nor calling it anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.72,0:26:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We let go of the images and the pictures.\NAnd instead we allow the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.72,0:26:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of what it is, the sensations of it,\Nto occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.16,0:26:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We let go resisting them\Nand as we do we let them run out.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.16,0:26:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What are we letting run out?\NWe're letting run out the energy field of desiringness,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.16,0:26:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy field of cravingness,\Nthat thing that seems to be coming out of your solar plexus
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.16,0:26:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of wantingness.\NWhen you look at wantingness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.16,0:26:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you will realize it is not a pleasurable experience.\NIt is not a pleasurable experience
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.16,0:26:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to stand there in this door window\Nand look at what is inside
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.16,0:26:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with a feeling of wanting, wanting, frustrated craving.\NWhen you look at it and cancel the content of what,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.16,0:26:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,whether it's diamonds, a fur coat,\Nor someone else's body,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.16,0:27:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,you will realize that the experience itself is unpleasant.\NTo want and not have is unpleasant.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.16,0:27:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,To want and not have at this moment.\NTo want a steak and smell it cooking
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.16,0:27:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but not being able to eat it\Nis really frustration.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.16,0:27:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hold a steak in front of a dog's nose\Nand just don't allow him to eat it,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.16,0:27:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,what is he experiencing?\NIs he experiencing happiness?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.16,0:27:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Is he glad to be alive?\NIf you keep it up long enough
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.52,0:27:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll end up with anger and rage\Nat the frustration of this desiringness.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.52,0:27:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not a pleasant feeling.\NIt is not that which contributes to sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.52,0:27:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The illusion is it is the desire\Nthat brings sex into my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.52,0:27:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because I want it.\NThe wanting and the desiring of it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.52,0:27:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is why I get to experience it.\NActually, the opposite is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.68,0:27:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the wantingness and the desiringness\Nwhich is blocking its coming into your life
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.68,0:27:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and your full enjoyment of it when it is there.\NThe letting go of this craving and this desiring then,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.41,0:28:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,what eventually happens is all the suppressed desiringness\Nthat you have repressed and suppressed in this lifetime
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.41,0:28:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and shoved down like a tank of compressed gas.\NThe pressure of this comes up
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.41,0:28:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and as you allow it to just be released,\Nallow it to flow through you
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.41,0:28:20.41,Default,,0,0,0,,without doing anything about it,\Nwithout opposing it,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.41,0:28:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,let go resisting experiencing it,\Nwhat happens is it begins to decompress.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.41,0:28:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, because there is a limited quantity of it,\Nit finally stops altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.60,0:28:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens to your life then\Nwhen the cravingness, the desiringness,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.60,0:28:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the obsession, the compulsion,\Nthe addiction to the wantingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.60,0:28:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the cravingness of this physicality,\Nof the sexuality happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.60,0:28:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens is you have peace.\NWhat a shocking thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.60,0:28:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Where there was a desiringness, a cravingness,\Na wantingness, a frustration, a feeling of lack,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.60,0:29:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,a feeling of not havingness,\Na feeling of low self-esteem
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.60,0:29:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because this is not being gratified,\Ninstead now you have a peacefulness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.60,0:29:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The thing just doesn't arise.\NThe same thing happens when you let go
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.60,0:29:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,your hunger and your craving and your desiringness\Nand your appetiting all the time for food.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.60,0:29:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That greediness finally lets go.\NYou see, we're talking really about a variety of greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.60,0:29:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not even talking about sex, are we?\NGreed can be a greed for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.60,0:29:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be a greed for that.\NBut the nature of it still,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.60,0:29:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of what the world calls sexuality,\Nis really a greediness, a wantingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.60,0:29:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a forever desiringness,\Nwhich runs people, runs their whole life, dominates it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.48,0:29:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of this, there is an inner state of peace,\Nan inner state of serenity,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.48,0:29:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as though the whole question has been handled,\Nas though it's no longer a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.48,0:29:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the problem now?\NThere is no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.84,0:30:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It no longer drives you crazy.\NIt no longer insults you, insults your integrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.84,0:30:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You no longer have to sell yourself out.\NThe person doesn't feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.93,0:30:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to now barter and trade their body\Nand their sexual expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.93,0:30:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a give and trade, an endless bargaining\Nthat goes on between men and women and sexual partners
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.03,0:30:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,for those that choose the same sex.\NThe tantalizing with it, the withholding,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.06,0:30:30.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the gift of it.\NNow you owe me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.06,0:30:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've paid me.\NI paid for your dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.06,0:30:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Now give me your body.\NThe endless trade-off and bargaining comes to an end.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.06,0:30:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,One is now free of being manipulated by that.\NLet's not forget that when we manipulate others,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.44,0:30:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we are equally manipulated in return.\NWhen we let go, manipulating through this sexuality,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.54,0:30:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,this variety of sexuality,\Nthat means we cannot be manipulated by it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.54,0:31:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So we become freer.\NYou see, once you are unattached,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.54,0:31:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,we move into the field of facing and coping with this problem,\Nour willingness to face and cope with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.54,0:31:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happens is we become unattached,\Nwe become released.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.15,0:31:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Down here we were entrapped and up here we are released.\NWhat is the release state?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.18,0:31:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't moved up to love yet, but we're on the way.\NWhat is the release state?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.18,0:31:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The release state means that I am so free of that now\Nthat if it happens in my life, that's terrific.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.18,0:31:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it doesn't happen in my life, I don't miss it.\NSo it's like if we have steak for dinner, fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.24,0:31:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we don't, that's okay too.\NWe'll have beans and salad.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.24,0:31:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So there may be a choice,\Nbut the first time we are now at the level
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.76,0:31:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of being able to make a choice.\NWe're not run by the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.76,0:31:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We're not run by this manipulation.\NEvery billboard doesn't send us to the store
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.76,0:31:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,to buy the chewing gum or whatever the pretty girl is doing.\NHmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.76,0:32:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Our willingness now to handle this, to transcend it,\Nmoves us up to an acceptance
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.76,0:32:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and allows us now to begin to feel adequate and confident.\NWe feel adequate because somehow there's an inner knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.85,0:32:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,that somehow the question has been finally answered in our life.\NWe know we're never going to be at the effect of that again.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.85,0:32:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not really going to run us.\NThat there's a certain sense of freedom comes in now.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.85,0:32:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So where there was frustration,\Nthere's now freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.85,0:32:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore we begin to feel adequate as a human being\Nand far more confident.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.85,0:32:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And we're willing then,\Nwilling to begin to move into a lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.85,0:32:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The world begins to seem more friendly.\NSee, when sex is something you bargain,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.85,0:32:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's something that your status depends on,\Nwhen it's your stock and trade in the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.85,0:32:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it hardly looks like a friendly world.\NIt really looks like a world of competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.85,0:33:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the world begins to look more okay.\NIt begins to look friendly.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.85,0:33:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It begins to look harmonious.\NWe begin to enjoy the opportunities for sexual expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.85,0:33:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,As we move in and out of acceptance then,\Nacceptance, we move into an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.75,0:33:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,where we're beginning to approach happiness,\Nan energy field which calibrates mathematically at 500
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.78,0:33:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,as compared to 0 for death, 30 for guilt,\Nand the ones we've talked about.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.78,0:33:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The beginning of happiness,\Na sense of mellowness,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.78,0:33:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a sense of feeling really good about ourselves\Nand with our behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.84,0:33:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This lovingness then,\Nthe beginning of nurture and support,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.84,0:33:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to forgive,\Nthe capacity to experience our own being
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.94,0:33:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,with this field of behavior\Nfrom a whole different point of view.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.94,0:33:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Energy field then resolves all the problems\Nthat arise in this lower energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.94,0:34:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,As we said before,\Neverything is experienced in consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.40,0:34:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's say for instance,\Nif your consciousness was colored blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.40,0:34:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,then everything you're experiencing\Nin your blue consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.40,0:34:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're experiencing is blueness.\NIf your consciousness is colored pink, let's say,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.47,0:34:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,then all your experience\Nis going to be experienced as pinkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.47,0:34:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So that this negativity then colors\Nthe whole experience of one's sexual life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.60,0:34:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's characteristic of these lower energy fields,\Nbecause they're coming from a lack,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.69,0:34:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,coming from lack,\Nis that everything is experienced as giving and getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.69,0:34:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, wanting means what?\NIt means the exchange of giving and getting.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.69,0:34:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you hear expressions about one's sexual life\Nthen in these lower energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.69,0:34:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of, did you get it last night?\NShe's worrying about whether she's going to give it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.69,0:34:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,He's worrying about whether he's going to get it.\NThe adolescent boys get together in the locker room
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.69,0:35:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and the question is, did you get it last night?\NAs you move up out of the lower energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.33,0:35:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of giving and getting,\Nyou move into the middle energy fields of doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.33,0:35:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, people are preoccupied\Nwith the doingness of sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.33,0:35:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, let's do it is the expression.\NLet's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.33,0:35:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, this style of doing\Nbecomes the preoccupation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.88,0:35:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have the endless,\Nsex manuals all talking about doingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.88,0:35:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They, of course, throw in some love,\Nthe more modern ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.88,0:35:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be nice to have love there too.\NThat should alter the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.88,0:35:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's considered to be romanticism.\NRomanticism and something that women require
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.00,0:35:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,to have happy sex.\NWomen are supposed to have an energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.23,0:35:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which she calls lovingness,\Nwhich generally is coming out of this
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.23,0:35:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,plus sentimentality and emotionality.\NSo she can now hold it from the viewpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.23,0:36:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of what she considers lovingness\Nso she can then indulge her desiringness
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.23,0:36:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,without experiencing guilt.\NThe energy field then of doingness
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.23,0:36:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the middle here.\NIt has to do with how well you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.48,0:36:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And so people then become anxious\Nabout their performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.48,0:36:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,If sex is something you do,\Nthen you should do it well in our society.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.48,0:36:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have the whole idea\Nof competitive performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.48,0:36:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea of competitiveness and performance.\NAnd out of performance anxiety comes
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.48,0:36:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,frigidity and lack of desire\Nand the various forms of impotence
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.48,0:36:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in which there is the anxiety about doingness,\Nperformance anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.52,0:36:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Will he like the way I do it?\NWill she like the way I do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.52,0:36:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Have I satisfied the other person?\NIt becomes sort of athletics,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.52,0:36:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of a refined athletics.\NSo from getting,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.09,0:36:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,from having,\Ngiving and getting,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.09,0:37:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,we move up to doing.\NAnd now what happens when we start moving up,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.09,0:37:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,when we let go of all that,\Nwhen we're no longer run by that,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.09,0:37:13.09,Default,,0,0,0,,then it becomes a way of how to be with someone.\NIt becomes of how you are with that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.09,0:37:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a way of sharing your being with that person.\NIt isn't what you give and get.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.16,0:37:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't how you perform,\Nas though there's a rating scale.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.16,0:37:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You know he got 82 on his doing list\Nlast night.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.16,0:37:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes a way of being with the person\Nin which the whole barter system falls out.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.60,0:37:40.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole performance system falls out.\NBecause this way of being with somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.60,0:37:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is no longer viewed from a lower position,\Nthe whole question of guilt falls out.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.60,0:37:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,All the moralistic questions are now answered.\NTo come from being with that other person,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.60,0:37:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to be with who they are,\Nnow the desire is to be with that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.60,0:38:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It means a connection within the heart.\NIt means the opening up of a space,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.60,0:38:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,a way of being with that person.\NSee the fear arises,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.31,0:38:13.31,Default,,0,0,0,,well if I let go of my desiringness,\Nif I let go of that wantingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.31,0:38:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't that mean that it will disappear from my life?\NResearch and experience and clinical experience
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.31,0:38:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,has shown that the opposite is true.\NThat the letting go of that desire
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.31,0:38:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that the letting go of the desiringness,\Nthe wantingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.31,0:38:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,which in itself in consciousness\Nsets up a resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.31,0:38:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,See that which we want and desire\Nsets up in the other person a resistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.31,0:38:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So when the salesman comes on to you\Nin his salesman style,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.85,0:38:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,you know he's going to want to sell you something.\NAnd when you get that he wants to sell you something,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.88,0:38:51.92,Default,,0,0,0,,what comes up in you,\Nhow are you going to resist that?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.92,0:38:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So instead of resistance,\Nthe pressure and the resistance,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.92,0:38:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the counterbalances,\Nwhich are going on in these lower energy fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.92,0:39:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in being with the person,\Nthen out of a lack of,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.92,0:39:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,a non-existence of desiringness and wantingness,\Nwhat happens?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.56,0:39:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We've created this space then\Nfor the energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.56,0:39:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,which are coming down through the body,\Nthrough the energy of life itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.56,0:39:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to express themselves\Nin that way which is most appropriate to the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.56,0:39:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of the energy coming\Nup,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.56,0:39:32.56,Default,,0,0,0,,the so-called Kundalini energy coming up the spine,\Ninstead of being run by the entrapment of that energy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.56,0:39:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,in the body's lower energy fields,\Nwe have the energy field of life itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.56,0:39:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is life itself,\Ncoming down through the body
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.56,0:39:48.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and opening up through the heart.\NThe letting go of the lower energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.45,0:39:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,opens the way for the higher energy field.\NThe opening up of joy,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.00,0:39:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the joyfulness,\Nthe lovingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.00,0:39:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to express itself.\NNow,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.00,0:40:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens in the relationship\Ninstead of performance
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.00,0:40:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is the desire to bring happiness and pleasure\Nand to support the other person's experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.00,0:40:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a compassion\Nto the love making.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.00,0:40:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,See, no longer is it worried about\Nperformance,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.00,0:40:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,no longer is it worried about\Nmorality,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.00,0:40:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,no longer is it struggling\Nwith moralistic questions
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.00,0:40:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because those have to do\Nwith being stuck in desiringness.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.00,0:40:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The negativity that arises out of that field\Nautomatically brings other negative thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.06,0:40:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And the negative thoughts are,\Nof course,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.06,0:40:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is this right?\NAm I being used?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.06,0:40:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I being exploited?\NAm I doing okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.06,0:40:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I built correctly?\NAm I in the right position?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.06,0:40:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Am I being like it's done in the movies?\NAm I doing it like it is in the performance manuals?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.06,0:40:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And there isn't much space there\Nfor the enjoyment.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.96,0:40:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't much space there.\NSpace there for the love of sexuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.96,0:41:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, what happens when you let go\Nthe desiring of sexuality?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.96,0:41:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,People say,\NBoy, if I let go of my desire,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.02,0:41:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't get any.\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.02,0:41:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Get any.\NWhat happens with letting go
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.02,0:41:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the desiringness for it\Nis a love for.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.02,0:41:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,A love for.\NA love for a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.02,0:41:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens when you let go desiring,\Nwanting to own something,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.08,0:41:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to have it,\Nto get it,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.08,0:41:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to master it,\Nto control it,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.08,0:41:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to clutch it.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.08,0:41:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Because when you want to desire it\Nand control it,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.08,0:41:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,even when you get it,\Nwhat comes up next
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.08,0:41:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,is the fear of losing it.\NRight?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.08,0:41:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You want the diamond bracelet,\Nyou have the diamond bracelet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.08,0:41:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What comes up next?\NThieves.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.08,0:41:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the obvious thing that comes up.\NThe fear of losing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.08,0:41:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the weeping and the wailing\Nwhen that which has been desired and gotten
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.08,0:41:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,is eventually lost.\NThe fear of losing comes up.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.82,0:41:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,When we move into the energy field then\Nof lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.82,0:41:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to be with,\Nwhat takes the place of desiring
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.82,0:42:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and wanting sex\Nis the loving it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.82,0:42:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to love sex for the first time.\NAnd as we said,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.82,0:42:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,love is non-judgmental.\NIt just is with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.82,0:42:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees its naturalness.\NIt's aware of the intrinsic innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.82,0:42:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It watches the animals now\Nfrom a different viewpoint.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.82,0:42:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It sees the expression\Nof the grace
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.82,0:42:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of the animalness.\NWhen it's out of a negative,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.98,0:42:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,condemning,\Nmoralistic energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.98,0:42:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you can then begin to experience\Nthe incredible beauty,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.98,0:42:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the perfection,\Nindeed the sacredness
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.98,0:42:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of this expression of what?\NThe expression of one's aliveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.98,0:42:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The thrill and joy and experience\Nof the energy field of one's aliveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.98,0:42:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to love sex.\NAnd so now we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.98,0:42:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the sexuality of love\Nand the love of sex
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.98,0:43:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,as an expression of love.\NApproaching sexuality
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.24,0:43:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of desire itself\Nis, as we said,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.30,0:43:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we saw that desire has sort of\Na negative energy field.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.46,0:43:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And a negative energy field\Nseems to bring in the propensity
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.52,0:43:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,for all of these negative energy fields\Nto come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.52,0:43:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So that it isn't just the desiringness,\Nbut it seems to bring with it
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.52,0:43:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a whole negative energy field,\Nwhich makes us prone to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.52,0:43:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The guilt and the apathy,\Nthe grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.52,0:43:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the fear,\Nthe anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.52,0:43:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the pridefulness,\Nthe anxiety about performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.88,0:43:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,When we're free of desire, therefore,\Nwe're released from guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.64,0:43:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We're released from remorse.\NWe're released from anticipation
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.64,0:43:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of maybe it won't happen.\NAll of these energies arising then
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.64,0:43:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,almost en masse,\Nalmost as a unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.68,0:43:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We let go worrying about\Nwhat's going to happen with sexuality
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.68,0:43:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,as we get older.\NThe whole question of
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.68,0:44:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,are you over the hill\Nwhen you're 40, 50, 60,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.68,0:44:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever over the hill means\Nin your cultural group.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.41,0:44:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The anxiety of giving and getting,\Nthe desire to keep,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.41,0:44:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to own,\Nto hold,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.41,0:44:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to manipulate,\Nto control,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.41,0:44:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,all of that disappears.\NIf the orientation now
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.41,0:44:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming from the heart,\Nif one has let go of desiringness,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.41,0:44:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,then it is only a way of being\Nwith another person.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.41,0:44:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And we find that sexuality continues on\Ninto old age unimpaired.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.44,0:44:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sexuality itself then\Ndoes not decline with age.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.48,0:44:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, its quality improves.\NAnd so clinically what we see
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.48,0:44:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is that sex gets better\Nthe older you get,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.48,0:44:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,much in the reverse of what\Nthe popular view may be.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.48,0:44:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The learning how to let go\Nof that which is trivial,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.48,0:44:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the letting go of the unimportant,\Nthe realization that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.48,0:44:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as you grow older\Nof what is important,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.48,0:45:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the quality of the experiencing\Nof the other person's energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.99,0:45:05.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As we said,\Nbecause all things are experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.99,0:45:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in consciousness,\Nas you get older and more mature
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.99,0:45:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and you own more and more\Nof the truth about yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.34,0:45:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you become increasingly interested\Nin what is the quality
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.34,0:45:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of the experience.\NThe quality of the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.34,0:45:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming out of the energy\Nthat is being experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.34,0:45:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in consciousness.\NAnd so in how to be with that person,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.34,0:45:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,what is attractive now\Nis that person's energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.34,0:45:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the physical body.\NThe physical body comes and goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.34,0:45:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But the quality of the energy\Nof being with that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.50,0:45:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And we begin to experience\Nthe energy of that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.50,0:45:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to notice\Nas we embrace the person
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.50,0:45:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that what we're attracted to\Nis their energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.50,0:45:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,As we clear up\Nall the manipulative things
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.50,0:45:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and manipulative games,\Nall the garbage that's in the space,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.50,0:46:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,as the space becomes increasingly clear,\Nas the integrity of our relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.50,0:46:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,with that person\Nbecomes progressively more important
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.50,0:46:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than trying to get\Nwhat one can get,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.50,0:46:15.49,Default,,0,0,0,,then what we become\Nincreasingly conscious of
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.49,0:46:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and we begin to experience\Nis the other person's energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.49,0:46:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, at the bottom of the box,\Nwe're not experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.52,0:46:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,their energy at all.\NWhat we're experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.52,0:46:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is our own energy.\NSexual attractiveness,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.52,0:46:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,as amazing as it may sound,\Ndoes not exist in the outer world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.52,0:46:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It is something that you\Nproject onto the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.52,0:46:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Sexual energy is something\Nthat you own.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.52,0:46:44.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you consider\Nto be attractive
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.52,0:46:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is something that you\Nproject onto the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.52,0:46:51.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So in one society,\Nbeing extremely slim
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.52,0:46:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is attractive.\NIn another society,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.52,0:46:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,being plump is attractive.\NBeing brunette or blonde
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.52,0:46:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or having a bone through your nose\Nor many rings
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.52,0:47:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or rings around your neck\Nor earlobes that are pulled long
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.52,0:47:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and things painted on your head\Nand your hair piled up,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.72,0:47:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of decorations\Nof the human body,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.72,0:47:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,these are only projections\Nof our own images
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.72,0:47:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are holding within.\NAnd so we haven't even owned it,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.84,0:47:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,you see.\NBelow this energy field here,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.84,0:47:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,we haven't even owned\Nthat we are the author of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.84,0:47:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that we're the source of our sexuality.\NWe think it's something
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.84,0:47:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that you like run across.\NYou know, the sailor running around
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.39,0:47:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,by himself from bar to bar,\Nthinking that he will run into that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:33.39,0:47:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,out there,\Nnot realizing that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.39,0:47:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the author,\NI am the owner of that
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.39,0:47:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,which is attractive to me.\NAnd as we move into
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.39,0:47:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,a higher energy field,\Nwe begin to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.39,0:47:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of the other person.\NNow, the physical attractiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.39,0:47:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't mean much of anything.\NYou can go to bed with somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.39,0:47:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,who,\Nphysically,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.39,0:47:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nhas a center page fold,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.39,0:48:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,might fall into\Nwhat the world calls attractive,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.39,0:48:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet the experience is repulsive.\NThe person's energy is abhorrent.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.39,0:48:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy,\Nnot what they say,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.39,0:48:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you could tape record what they say.\NYou could type it out
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.39,0:48:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,as a transcript and read it.\NSounds okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.39,0:48:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You could take a photograph\Nand say,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.39,0:48:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is this person attractive?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.39,0:48:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it such a\Ndisenjoyable experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.39,0:48:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is there no desire to repeat it?\NYou realize it was
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.39,0:48:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,the fulfillment of\Nsome kind of a fantasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.39,0:48:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,There was nothing there,\Nno energy there.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.39,0:48:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What's it like to make love\Nwith somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.39,0:48:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in a reverse negative energy field\Nwho's coming from anxiety
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.39,0:48:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and fear\Nand low self-esteem?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.39,0:48:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not particularly pleasurable.\NIt ends up as sort of therapy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.39,0:48:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You know,\Nyou're really doing therapy
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.39,0:48:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,with the other person.\NYou get so preoccupied
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.39,0:48:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,with their unhappiness\Nabout the whole experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.87,0:48:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,As we move into lovingness then,\Nand we clear this out,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.87,0:48:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens then is\Nthe desire to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.87,0:48:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the other person's energy.\NWe get a feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.87,0:49:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So in that clear space,\Nthe masculinity is attracted
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.87,0:49:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to that femininity,\Nand it's almost as though
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.87,0:49:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,universal man\Nis with universal woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.87,0:49:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though one transcends\Nthe personality,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.87,0:49:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire to be with\Nthat energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.16,0:49:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,which we call the feminine\Nor the masculine.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.16,0:49:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now that the experience\Nbecomes totally different,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.96,0:49:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of a localized\Nphysical experience
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.96,0:49:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,accompanied by some emotionality,\Nthe beating of the heart
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.96,0:49:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the physicality\Nof the emotions,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.96,0:49:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,instead there is now\Na quite different feeling,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.96,0:49:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a feeling of expansiveness,\Na feeling of that oneness.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.96,0:49:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And where does sex arise?\NIt arises spontaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.96,0:49:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the being\Nwith the energy of that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.96,0:49:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,A second before,\Nthere was no thought of sex
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.18,0:50:00.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in either one's mind.\NThey're waiting for the toast
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.28,0:50:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to come out of the toaster.\NAnd then there's the embrace,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.28,0:50:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and if that embrace\Nis done in a field that is clear,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.63,0:50:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,in other words,\Nthe partners have let go
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.63,0:50:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of any withholds of resentment\Nand things that they're obstructing
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.63,0:50:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,their being with each other,\Nthen out of the embrace itself
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.14,0:50:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,arises the desire,\Nthe desire now
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.52,0:50:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,is of a totally different nature.\NIt's the desire to be with
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.52,0:50:35.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and experience that person\Nand their energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.68,0:50:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The spontaneity of it\Narises out of the space,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.68,0:50:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,not out of desiringness,\Nbut out of the sense of aliveness,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.68,0:50:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the energy of being\Nwith the space of that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.32,0:50:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a diffuse overall experience.\NSo instead of a local anatomical experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.32,0:50:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,limited anatomically\Nto a small area of the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.32,0:51:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,accompanied by emotionality,\Ninstead,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.32,0:51:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,there is an overall aliveness.\NIt's as though the energy field
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.32,0:51:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,encompasses and surrounds\Nthe two of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.32,0:51:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the sexuality\Nis arising out of the energy field itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.32,0:51:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to have nothing to do\Nwith the personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.32,0:51:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to have nothing at all\Nto do with that solar plexus wantingness
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.32,0:51:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or desiringness,\Nor that genital excitability
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.32,0:51:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,which comes out of desire\Nand its frustration.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.32,0:51:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead is the joy\Nof being with that energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.32,0:51:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the gratefulness for the opportunity\Nto be with that energy
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.32,0:51:45.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the high joy and pleasure\Nof that which is a sense of alness,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.32,0:51:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of completeness.\NAt the very moment
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.90,0:51:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,that this desiringness arises\Nin this type of energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.90,0:51:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it is already simultaneously complete.\NSo if the phone rings
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.90,0:52:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and the whole set is interrupted,\Nit can be dropped instantly
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.32,0:52:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with no feeling of loss.\NThere's no feeling of loss
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.32,0:52:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,because the sense of completion\Nwithin the heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.32,0:52:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the oneness,\Nthe unification has already occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.32,0:52:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,\Nwhen we come from wantingness
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.32,0:52:18.41,Default,,0,0,0,,or desiringness,\Nif you hold a steak
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.41,0:52:21.41,Default,,0,0,0,,in front of a dog's nose\Nand then you take it away,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.41,0:52:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,he will feel loss,\Nhe will feel grief,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.41,0:52:27.37,Default,,0,0,0,,he will feel anger.\NIn a state of being
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.37,0:52:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,at one with another person,\Nthe satisfaction is running simultaneously
Dialogue: 0,0:52:32.37,0:52:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,with the experience.\NWonderful phenomena
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.37,0:52:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,that begins to happen in our life\Nwhen we let go
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.37,0:52:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of any particular appetite.\NWhen we let go of being run
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.37,0:52:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,by any appetite,\Nit's as though the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.37,0:52:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is complete at all times.\NWe'll notice that with weight reduction,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.40,0:52:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that if we let go of\Nand disappear that hungriness,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.40,0:53:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that wanting of the food,\Nthe being run by hunger,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.40,0:53:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,what happens is that\Nthe sense of wanting to eat,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.33,0:53:10.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the desire to eat,\Nnow arise out of the eating itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.33,0:53:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,When we sit down to eat,\Nthere still is no feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.33,0:53:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of hunger or appetite.\NBut as we begin to eat,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.33,0:53:20.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the enjoyment is enormous.\NIf, however,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.33,0:53:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the doorbell rings\Nright in the middle
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.33,0:53:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,of eating your steak,\Nyou can leave the meal,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.33,0:53:29.33,Default,,0,0,0,,go and be with a friend,\Nand there's no feeling of loss,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.33,0:53:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,no feeling of lack.\NIt's as though the completion
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.33,0:53:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,accompanies the enjoyment.\NSo instead of coming
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.33,0:53:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,from a wantingness,\Nit's always as though
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.33,0:53:40.33,Default,,0,0,0,,you're just this side\Nof the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.33,0:53:45.40,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to push the next second.\NYou know how that is in sex,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.40,0:53:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,how that is with eating.\NYou're always anticipating
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.40,0:53:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the next biteful.\NYou're anticipating
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.40,0:53:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the next sensation.\NYou're always anticipating.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.40,0:53:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you're reaching\Nso that there's always
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.40,0:54:00.40,Default,,0,0,0,,an internal strain\Nbetween what is happening
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.40,0:54:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,right this second\Nand what you desire
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.40,0:54:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and want and crave\Nto happen in the next second.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.40,0:54:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Once that wanting, craving,\Ndesiring is let go of,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.32,0:54:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,what's happening now\Nis the feeling of being
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.32,0:54:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,with the exact moment\Nso that each moment
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.32,0:54:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is complete and total in itself.\NBecause of its completeness,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:24.32,0:54:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,it can be stopped any second\Nwith no feeling of loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.32,0:54:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're in a very\Nhigh energy state,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.57,0:54:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in a state of high energy,\Njoyfulness, blissfulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.57,0:54:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no feeling of loss.\NSomebody can turn off
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.57,0:54:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the television set\Nof the program you've been watching,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.57,0:54:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,no feeling of loss.\NWhy is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.57,0:54:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you're experiencing.\NThe nature of your consciousness now
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.57,0:54:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is one of coming from completeness\Nall the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.57,0:54:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,To be with that person now,\Nto feel it one with their energy,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.57,0:55:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to feel that acceptance,\Nthat aliveness of that oneness
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.57,0:55:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is at the very moment\Nof his experience
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.57,0:55:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,already complete.\NThere is no have to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.60,0:55:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,continue this experience\Nbecause the sense of completion
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.60,0:55:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the anticipated future.\NThe pleasure of the eating
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.44,0:55:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the anticipation\Nof the next biteful.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.44,0:55:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That kind of sexuality then\Nhas an internal strain.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.66,0:55:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It disallows the expansion\Ninto the infiniteness
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.66,0:55:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,which rightfully accompanies\Nthat experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.66,0:55:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The letting go of that desiringness then\Nallows us to be completely at one,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.69,0:55:48.69,Default,,0,0,0,,completely content.\NEach moment then arises spontaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.69,0:55:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Each moment seems to be arising\Nof its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.69,0:55:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Within the embrace,\Nthe experience now is happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.95,0:56:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though it's a movie unfolding\Nand you are a participant in the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.95,0:56:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You are enjoying the unfolding\Nof this spontaneity.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.95,0:56:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What's happened is\Nyou've owned yourself back as source.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.25,0:56:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of putting it outside of yourself\Nas something to get,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.25,0:56:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,you've owned it as something that you are.\NIt is your purpose
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.25,0:56:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and your way of being\Nwith that way about yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.25,0:56:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience is coming from within you.\NTherefore, there is no gap
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.25,0:56:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,between that which you are\Nand the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.25,0:56:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You see?\NWhen we're coming from a lower energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.25,0:56:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like you are here\Nand that which is desired is over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.25,0:56:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And the desire then is pictured as\Nsomehow coming across
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.25,0:56:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and reducing the distance and the space.\NBut there's always that feeling of space
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.25,0:57:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,between that which you think you are,\Nyour desiringness,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:00.25,0:57:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and that which you want.\NThere's the subject and the object.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.25,0:57:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As we let go of that and become free of that,\Nthen we begin to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.83,0:57:14.83,Default,,0,0,0,,life spontaneously unfolding\Nof its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.83,0:57:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to feel a reverence\Nfor the nature of this experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.83,0:57:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Life becomes\Nthat which is described by the mystic.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.83,0:57:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,What is a mystic?\NA mystic is a person who has really
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.83,0:57:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,let go of that desiringness\Nand is experiencing from second to second
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.83,0:57:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the completeness, the totality,\Nand in it the exquisite beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.83,0:57:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore a reverence\Nand the sacredness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.83,0:57:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore now the relationship becomes\Nan expression of that which is sacred,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.83,0:57:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,the enjoyment of the exquisite\Nsense of aliveness.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:50.83,0:57:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like it has transcended the world.\NHow has it transcended the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.83,0:58:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We could say that the world is that\Nwhich is constantly changing,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.53,0:58:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that which begins and that which ends,\Nthat which is limited,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.53,0:58:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that which limits us.\NAnd if we identify with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.53,0:58:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,then it limits our experience\Nto that local wanting, cravingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.53,0:58:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If we let that go then,\Nthat energy field which begins to come
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.53,0:58:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,through the heart,\Nwhich unites us with that other person
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.53,0:58:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,in this spontaneous joyfulness,\Nmeans that we've really transcended the world
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.53,0:58:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,because now the energy that we're experiencing\Nis that which is infinite.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.82,0:58:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes an infinite experience.\NWe're not talking about this philosophically.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.82,0:58:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We're talking about it experientially.\NSo that the sexual experience now expands.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.82,0:58:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of a local genital phenomena,\Nwe notice the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.82,0:58:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,throughout the entire body.\NFrom the entire body it may now be
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.82,0:58:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to expand to like a space around the body.\NIt seems to be as though the whole room
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.82,0:59:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is having an orgasm.\NIt seems as though some kind of an infinite space
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.14,0:59:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is the source.\NAnd the body is merely expressing
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.14,0:59:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,what is happening in that space.\NThe body then becomes like the marionette
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.14,0:59:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,which is acting out\Nwhat is going on in an invisible realm,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.14,0:59:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is infinite.\NSo the energy of this now,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.72,0:59:29.75,Default,,0,0,0,,we don't have our survival\Non anything that is limited.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.75,0:59:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, we're experiencing that which is unlimited.\NCan we say that love is unlimited?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.97,0:59:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If we look around us,\Nwe see lovingness everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.97,0:59:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The expression of lovingness.\NIt has no beginning, it has no end.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.97,0:59:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no limitation.\NThe only thing that limits it
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.97,0:59:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,is our willingness to experience it.\NOur willingness to open ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.97,0:59:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,up to it.\NIt's like an infinite ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.97,1:00:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And so when we open ourselves up to it\Nby letting go of that which opposes it,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.97,1:00:08.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we become an expression of that lovingness.\NWe experience it then as an infinite state
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.97,1:00:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that transcends the personality,\Nthat transcends time and space.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.13,1:00:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The greatest aphrodisiac\Nis that inner sense of aliveness.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.13,1:00:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,As that aliveness intensifies,\Nit's as though that sense of aliveness
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.26,1:00:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,awakens all of us,\Nthe totality of us.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.26,1:00:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That feeling of loveness,\Ngodness,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.26,1:00:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is the greatest aphrodisiac of all.\NAnd so we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.55,1:00:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the sexuality of the heart\Ninstead of the sexuality of the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.55,1:00:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The sexuality that arises out of the heart.\NAnd here when we're talking about heart,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.61,1:00:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,we're not talking about the physical organ.\NWe're talking about heart
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.61,1:00:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with a capital H.\NHeart, that which is all-encompassing,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.74,1:01:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is all-diffuse,\Nthat which is all-inclusive,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.74,1:01:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that intense sense of aliveness,\Nthe exquisite pleasure
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.74,1:01:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,in the experience of our own existence,\Nexpressed now within the energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.74,1:01:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of being with someone\Nwhose energy matches yours,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.74,1:01:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,its polar opposite.\NWe get to experience in this space then,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.64,1:01:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that opposite within us\Nwhich we have not experienced before.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.64,1:01:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We allow then to experience\Nin the man his own feminine.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.92,1:01:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He then owns it in the experience\Nand the embrace.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.92,1:01:41.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman experiences\Nthat energy field within herself
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.92,1:01:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,coming back to her through the man.\NAnd therefore there is that sense of oneness
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.92,1:01:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and that completeness,\Nthe magic of that embrace.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.92,1:01:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The magic of that embrace\Nis the joining of these two energy fields,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.92,1:01:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the masculine and the feminine,\Nas an expression of their oneness
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.92,1:02:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,out of that intense feeling of aliveness and joy.\NThat settles all the problems
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.79,1:02:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that man has talked about\Nhaving to do with sexuality
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.79,1:02:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because in that inner experience,\Nin the subtlety of that inner experience,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.79,1:02:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is the reconnecting\Nwith the joy of one's innocence.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.79,1:02:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole question about\Nwhether God approves of sex,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.79,1:02:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,which is created by the intellect,\Nby man's left brain,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.79,1:02:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,what he is asking is,\Ndoes God approve of carnality?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:32.79,1:02:37.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Does God approve of that\Nwhich is coming out of a negative energy field?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.79,1:02:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,In the experience of that aliveness\Nand that oneness,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.20,1:02:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in the experience of joy,\Nas one moves up to an infinite state
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.46,1:02:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of inner peace and completion,\Nbecause completion is peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.46,1:02:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,what is peace but that sense\Nof absolute oneness,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.46,1:03:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the rejoining with the One?\NAnd so, within that sexuality
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.46,1:03:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which arises out of the heart\Nis the return to the experience
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.46,1:03:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of being with the One\Nthat gives it its mystical transcendent quality,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.46,1:03:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,its sense of everywhere-ness,\Nits sense of completion.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.46,1:03:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though it speaks for all men\Nand for all women for all time.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.46,1:03:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The inner feeling that one is all men\Nand all women for all time.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.46,1:03:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Wondering if one is Adam or Eve.\NMany people have had that thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.62,1:03:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When that sense of oneness comes in,\Nit's as though one transcends all of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.68,1:03:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,One has been all of men forever.\NOne has been all of women forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.07,1:03:45.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We own the source.\NWe are that,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.07,1:03:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and out of which that experience arises.\NNo longer at the effect of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.07,1:03:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but the expression of that.\NIt's incredible sacredness and its beauty.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.77,1:03:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The subtlety of that inner experience.\NWe look within.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.77,1:04:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we make this practical?\NDoes it sound like fantasy?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.99,1:04:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it sound like the mystical, the unreal?\NDoes it sound like the sex of unicorns perhaps?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.99,1:04:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Not real men and women?\NThere are certain ways in which one can
Dialogue: 0,1:04:13.79,1:04:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,practically move into it.\NOne way to get unfocused
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.79,1:04:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,from the physicality and the body\Narises out of an ancient
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.79,1:04:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,traditional meditative technique.\NAnd it's really worth trying,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:25.79,1:04:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and you'll be amazed at the results.\NNext time when you're having sexual experience,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.04,1:04:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,focus your attention and keep it there\Nthroughout the entire experience
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.04,1:04:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,one inch below your navel.\NJust try it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.08,1:04:44.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a point the Japanese call the hara,\None inch below the navel.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.08,1:04:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's used in martial arts\Nwhere one focuses one's centeredness.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.08,1:04:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of paying attention\Nto the movements of the body,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.08,1:04:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of paying attention\Nto the manipulations,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:55.08,1:04:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the endless anxieties,\Nconcentrate, fix your attention right there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.08,1:05:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold your attention no matter what is happening.\NAnd you'll find that you're somewhat removed now.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.08,1:05:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this somewhat removed state\Nwhere you become somewhat the participant observer,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.08,1:05:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the entire experience now takes on\Na whole different dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.20,1:05:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It is now sort of happening within you.\NBut instead of being focused into the local,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.43,1:05:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you're experiencing now\Nfrom a more generalized energy field.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.43,1:05:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Try that as a way to move\Nfrom that local experience
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.43,1:05:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,on up to the heart.\NJust move into that point called the hara,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.65,1:05:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,H-A-R-A,\Nand you'll notice the change of quality
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.10,1:05:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,of the experience.\NAnd then you'll see it's what we're talking about
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.10,1:05:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,is quality.\NWe're talking about quality
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.10,1:05:55.10,Default,,0,0,0,,because when you move out of the localization,\Nyou're moving into a different energy field
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.10,1:06:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and the entire experience is then of one of expansion,\Nan expanded experience,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.10,1:06:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,much greater, greater in intensity,\Nmuch more fulfilling,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.10,1:06:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,much more gratifying,\Nsubsequent to which one feels joyful and grateful.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.10,1:06:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Grateful instead of satisfied.\NThe difference is gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.36,1:06:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the energy field of gratitude.\NGratitude is up here about 540,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.36,1:06:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,akin to joy.\NInstead of satisfaction of desire,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.36,1:06:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which leaves people often with a sense of loss.\NAnd the Latin phrase meaning after intercourse,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.36,1:06:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there is sadness.\NWhy after intercourse is there sadness?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.36,1:06:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Or sexuality without a sexual partner.\NWhy does it leave you with a sense of sadness?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.36,1:06:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,A sense of loss.\NAnd it was becoming,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.36,1:06:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,as it was coming from that sense\Nof non-completion,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.36,1:06:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that sense of lack.\NIt was putting the source of one's sexuality
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.36,1:06:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,out there someplace in the world\Ninstead of reowning it
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.36,1:07:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,as part of that which you are.\NThe sense of innocence that arises
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.64,1:07:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,then puts you back in the Garden of Eden\Nas though you have just
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.64,1:07:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,uneaten,\Nuneaten
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.64,1:07:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the tree of good and bad,\Ngood and evil.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.38,1:07:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as though it takes you out of\Nthe field of carnality
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.44,1:07:24.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and puts you back into the innocence,\Nthe awareness of the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.44,1:07:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which you really are.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.54,1:07:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the greatest of all human experiences.\NIn it,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.30,1:07:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,we demonstrate that whole principle.\NThat it isn't the events of life,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.30,1:07:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it isn't what's happening,\Nbut how we are with those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.30,1:07:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's how we decide to be with that\Nthat determines the nature of the experience.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.30,1:07:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it's a guilt-inducing,\Nfrustrating,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.30,1:07:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,anxiety-provoking,\Nneurotic type
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.30,1:07:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of a dysfunction,\Nor whether it is one of the greatest
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.30,1:08:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of all human experiences.\NAll arises of how we decide
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.30,1:08:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to be with that.\NHow we decide to hold that
Dialogue: 0,1:08:05.36,1:08:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,within our experience.\NWhat context we're coming from
Dialogue: 0,1:08:09.36,1:08:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,about who we really are\Nand the nature of human experience.
